goals.rationale: This helps us understand if there is a correlation between distance and delay, and if longer flights tend to have more delays.

goals.rationale: This tells us about the range of flight distances and if there are any common distances.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True)
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    delays_by_airport = data.groupby('origin')['delay'].count().reset_index()
    delays_by_airport = delays_by_airport.sort_values(by='delay', ascending=False)
    if len(delays_by_airport) > 20:
        delays_by_airport = delays_by_airport[:20]
    ax = sns.barplot(x='origin', y='delay', data=delays_by_airport)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which airports have the most delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='ignore')
    chart = sns.histplot(data=data, x='distance', kde=False)
    chart.set(xlabel='Distance (miles)', ylabel='Count')
    chart.xaxis.label.set_rotation(45)

        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight distances?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
